  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "Which of the following types of ocular injuries can result from blunt trauma to the eye?\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t1)\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t2)\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t3)\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t4)",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "2 and 4"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "1 and 2"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "3 and 1"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "All of the Above"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: D) All of the Above</strong></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p>All of the given presentations can result from <strong>Blunt trauma to the eye.</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:514px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ol>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Hyphema</li>\n\t\t\t</ol>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\"><img alt=\"-\" data-author=\"Imrankabirhossain\" data-hash=\"1879\" data-license=\"CC BY SA 3.0\" data-source=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Total_hyphema.jpg\" data-tags=\"March2025\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/nsZ3HgcHF0gIi4iHgWgm1742987998.png\" /></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>2. Descemet's <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"34cd707428169277719272942b7905\">membrane</span> tear</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\"><img alt=\"-\" data-author=\"Papaioannou, Lamprini & Papathanassiou, Miltiadis. \" data-hash=\"1880\" data-license=\"CC BY 4.0\" data-source=\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/Extensive-descemets-membrane-rupture_fig1_313615891\" data-tags=\"March2025\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/kQNsB6SSztdafk9R4siw1742987999.png\" /></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>3. Vossius ring</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\"><img alt=\"-\" data-author=\"Klaeger, Andres & Herbort, Carl.\" data-hash=\"1881\" data-license=\"NA\" data-source=\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/Right-and-left-anterior-segment-after-the-anterior-uveitis-started-in-the-left-eye-A_fig2_23317095\" data-tags=\"March2025\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/1aP2DF4cCfrpoD6EN5T91742987999.png\" /></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>4. Lens subluxation</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\"><img alt=\"-\" data-author=\"Chen, Tianhui & Deng, Michael & Zhang, Min & Chen, Jiahui & Chen, Zexu & Jiang, Yongxiang. \" data-hash=\"1882\" data-license=\"CC BY 4.0\" data-source=\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/349031986_Visual_outcomes_of_lens_subluxation_surgery_with_Cionni_modified_capsular_tension_rings_in_Marfan_syndrome\" data-tags=\"March2025\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/3MSFWN7elQUB7cfV7z2C1742987999.png\" /></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Blunt trauma (also known as non-penetrating or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"324b1bfa7816927771834f9e3f6704\">blunt</span> force trauma)</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Cause: </strong>A strong impact, a fall, or a physical assault with a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"324b1bfa7816927771834f9e3f6704\">blunt</span> object resulting from sports injuries and assaults.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Features: </strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Conjunctiva: </strong>Subconjunctival hemorrhage</li>\n\t<li><strong>Cornea:</strong> Abrasions, corneal oedema, <strong>Descemet's <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"34cd707428169277719272942b7905\">membrane</span> tears</strong><strong>.</strong> </li>\n\t<li><strong>Hyphaema</strong><strong>: </strong>Blood in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1ba6a9cfe11692777181950edd7a6d\">anterior</span> chamber leading to corneal staining. </li>\n\t<li><strong>Iris: </strong>Iridodialysis (dehiscence of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6e53fc929616927771900fbab3617f\">iris</span> from the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1be9f55b2d1692777184b9d813b17e\">ciliary</span> body at its root), <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6e53fc929616927771900fbab3617f\">iris</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1a73a42f071692777199a59120f494\">sphincter</span> tear,</li>\n\t<li><strong>Ciliary body: </strong>Ciliary body tear leading to angle recession.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Lens: </strong><strong>Vossious Ring</strong> (in the shape of the pupil), <strong>Rosette-shaped cataract</strong> (flower-shaped opacity), <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e53b153fb316927771996481a3e88f\">subluxation</span> of lens.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Globe <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e73553a3a5169277719787fd5f4680\">rupture</span> </strong>(caused by severe <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"324b1bfa7816927771834f9e3f6704\">blunt</span> trauma, indicated by <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6e53fc929616927771900fbab3617f\">iris</span> prolapse)</li>\n\t<li><strong>Vitreous haemorrhage</strong>: Pigment cells<strong> (‘tobacco dust’)</strong> can be seen floating in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1ba6a9cfe11692777181950edd7a6d\">anterior</span> vitreous.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Choroidal rupture</strong></li>\n\t<li><strong>Retina: </strong><strong>Commotio Retinae (also known as Berlin's oedema)</strong>, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fb7a2c30e416927771972f7df6f8c0\">retinal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5755720cc31692777186c957a0feb7\">dialysis</span> (disinsertion from <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4ddf5d11d71692777194fac8ecc625\">ora</span> serrata), giant <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fb7a2c30e416927771972f7df6f8c0\">retinal</span> Tear <strong>(horseshoe shaped)</strong>, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ebad8eb48c1692777191b5de5d04a1\">macular</span> hole.</li>\n\t<li>Injury to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1b9a354cdb1692777194802683234d\">optic</span> nerve</li>\n\t<li><strong>Traumatic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2d9476094c16927771933bcb162f19\">neuropathy</span> </strong>with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3e48c7feaa169277718485430831dd\">chorioretinal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e9dcc3d4241692777198c7030bf313\">scarring</span> (decreased visual acuity, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d01e44abab16927772010db8725801\">visual field</span> defect, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4dd3bdfe1d1692777180deb3103555\">afferent</span> pupillary defect, colour, and brightness).</li>\n</ul>",
