    {
      "text": "A patient presents with a full-thickness corneal wound caused by a nail. Which of the following is the most likely complication if the injury is left untreated?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Ring abscess of the cornea"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Retinal detachment"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Glaucoma"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Strabismus"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: A) Ring <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5618681fbe16927771804370383aaa\">abscess</span> of the cornea</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Untreated <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55b31d659b16927771958a15837b10\">penetrating</span> injuries can introduce microorganisms, leading to severe infections like a ring <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5618681fbe16927771804370383aaa\">abscess</span> of the cornea, a sight-threatening condition.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:611px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Penetrating Eye Injury</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Definition</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>A <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55b31d659b16927771958a15837b10\">penetrating</span> injury enters the eye without exiting, resulting in no exit wound.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Causes</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Sharp objects such as sharpened pencils <strong>(most common cause in children)</strong>, needles, knives, nails, screws, glass, etc.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Damage Mechanisms</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Tearing and structural disruption</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pathogens enter through open wounds, leading to <strong>ring abscesses</strong>, corneal sloughing, iridocyclitis, endophthalmitis, panophthalmitis, etc. <strong>(Option A)</strong></li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t<img alt=\"-\" data-author=\"NA\" data-hash=\"1913\" data-license=\"NA\" data-source=\"NA\" data-tags=\"March2025\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/SZiDOvyeysZ3mXfYjesN1742988864.png\" /><br />\n\t\t\t </td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Prognosis </strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>It depends on the severity of the injury and the complications that arise secondary to the injury.</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Influenced by:</p>\n\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Initial visual acuity</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Presence of a relative pupillary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"359a8718a61692777185568ac80abb\">defect</span> (RAPD)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Presence of an <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1ba26fe8171692777190a867ec47c7\">intraocular</span> foreign body</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Presence of infection</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Presence of a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fb7a2c30e416927771972f7df6f8c0\">retinal</span> injury or detachment.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>Retinal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2b005085881692777186cf95c3ad51\">detachment</span> (Option B) </strong>is more commonly associated with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"324b1bfa7816927771834f9e3f6704\">blunt</span> trauma rather than <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55b31d659b16927771958a15837b10\">penetrating</span> injuries.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Glaucoma (Option C</strong>) is a potential late <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8a6b09beac1692777184b08a2b5766\">complication</span> but not the immediate concern in this scenario.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Strabismus (Option D) </strong>refers to eye misalignment, which arises from muscle or nerve dysfunction, not corneal trauma.</p>\n\n<p><br />\n </p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
